comment: A 24 Second Violation is correctly called.

LHH shows Pachulia (MIL) starts upward motion into Dragic (MIA) while he is in the air going by. Since Pachulia did not draw Dragic into the air towards him, no automatic foul and contact deemed incidental. (See POE memo 12/12/14.)

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that MIA and MIL simultaneously touched the ball as it went OOB (which would have resulted in a jumpball) was overturned and MIA was awarded possession.
Bayless (MIL) commits a take foul on Wade (MIA).
Wade (MIA) breaks the plane of the FT line before the ball hits the rim.
Haslem (MIA) allows Middleton (MIL) to land after attempting the jumpshot.
Walker (MIA) makes contact with Ilyasova's (MIL) lower body as he secures the rebound and goes up for the jumpshot all in the same motion.
LATR shows Antetokounmpo (MIL) and Beasley (MIA) engage before ball hits the rim.
Beasley (MIA) maintains legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket by Bayless (MIL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Middleton's (MIL) three-point shot was released prior to the game clock expiring was upheld.
